						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up in front of the Āñjaneya temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 142[7], Raktākshi, Māgha śu. 11, Thursday, corresponding to 1505 A.D., January 16.</p>						

						<p>Records the consecreation of an image of Hanuman and a grant of land for providing food offerings to the deity by Chidurele-Ayyaṅgāru, for the merit of his parents Allāḍayya and Anantamma.</p>						

						</summary>
